    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p><b>Acceptance Criteria:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>User can access a login form.</li>
	<li>User can enter their registered email address.</li>
	<li>User can enter their password.</li>
	<li>The system validates the entered credentials against user data.</li>
	<li>Upon successful login:
	<ul>
		<li>The user is redirected to their account dashboard or the app's main screen.</li>
		<li>A session is established for the user, allowing them to access app functionalities.</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Upon failed login due to incorrect credentials:
	<ul>
		<li>The system displays a clear error message indicating invalid login attempt.</li>
		<li>The error message should not reveal specific details like whether the username or password is incorrect (security best practice).</li>
		<li>There should be a limit on the number of consecutive login attempts to prevent brute-force attacks (define a specific number based on security policy).</li>
		<li>After exceeding the login attempt limit, the system temporarily locks the account or requires additional verification (e.g., captcha).</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
</ul>


<p><b>Optional Acceptance Criteria:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>User can choose to "Remember Me" on the login form to store login credentials securely for future access. (Consider security implications and user consent for this feature)</li>
	<li>User can access a "Forgot Password" functionality to reset their password if forgotten. (Link this to a separate user story for Forgot Password)</li>
</ul>

