    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>As a user, I want to receive a confirmation email after successful registration. </p>

<p><b>Acceptance Criteria:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>Upon successful registration form submission, the system automatically generates a confirmation email.</li>
	<li>The email is sent to the user's registered email address.</li>
	<li>The email subject line clearly indicates it's a confirmation email (e.g., "Welcome to Carrefour! Confirm Your Account").</li>
	<li>The email body contains:
	<ul>
		<li>A greeting message for the user (e.g., "Hi <span class="error">&#91;User Name&#93;</span>").</li>
		<li>A brief explanation of the purpose of the email (e.g., "Thank you for registering with Carrefour").</li>
		<li>A clear call to action with a verification link (e.g., "Click the link below to verify your account and activate your access").</li>
		<li>The verification link should be unique to the user and time-bound (e.g., valid for 24 hours).</li>
		<li>Information on what happens after clicking the link (e.g., "Your account will be activated and you can start shopping!").</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li>The email footer includes standard information like company contact details and unsubscribe options.t</li>
</ul>

            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
    </table>

